29:19.970 --> 29:22.536
theoretical stuff. They'd have to show an ability 
to do it, which means that they'd have to have a good

29:22.556 --> 29:30.975
background in math and physics and geology and an 
interest in the field. So you'd make it

29:32.258 --> 29:35.385
ability-based, talent-based. primarily yeah 
right yeah I think because you can get the ability

29:36.209 --> 29:50.421
most anywhere you know I was certainly wouldn't do 
it racially or you wouldn't do it on a need basis

29:36.209 --> 29:50.421
financial need as much as ability Well, I would 
rather it went to somebody who needed it, but at the

29:51.616 --> 29:59.887
same time, I would presume that whoever's asking 
for it does need it. Otherwise, if they don't need

29:59.907 --> 30:02.711
it, I would say, hey, don't take it. Clearly, yeah, 
right. Need should be a consideration, but not the

30:07.077 --> 30:10.602
most important consideration. I wouldn't give it 
to a bad needy student, let a good, not so needy

30:11.463 --> 30:17.691
student go by. Last question. What feelings do you 
have in your heart today about Texas A&M? Oh, I

30:25.648 --> 30:26.990
think it was a great place. It was a good place to be. 
